text.section:
Any person, his agent, or employee who sells or possesses with intent to sell a secondhand watch shall deliver to the buyer a written invoice which sets forth:
The name and address of the seller;
The name and address of the buyer;
The date of the sale;
The name of the watch or its maker;
The serial number or, if none, any other distinguishing number or identification mark on the case and the movement of the watch; and
Whether any serial number or any other distinguishing number or identification mark has been erased, defaced, removed, altered, or covered.
